HEADWORD: Contubernial
<hw>Con`tu*ber"ni*al</hw>
<pr>(k⟦ocr⟧n`t⟦usl⟧*b⟦etil⟧r"n⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>contubernalis</ets> a tent companion, fr.
<ets>contubernium</ets> tent companionship.]</ety> <def>Living or
messing together; familiar; in companionship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Humble folk ben Christes friends: they ben <qex>contubernial</qex>
with the Lord, thy King.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contumacious</ent>⟦br⟧
